## Why This Is Asked

This question tests triage of a mixed HTTP, MongoDB, Vault path and teaches safe caching of per-request secrets, a common beginner pitfall.

## Key Concepts

- Latency breakdown and instrumentation
- Vault per-request secret calls vs caching
- MongoDB indexing and query patterns
- Safe TTL-based cache and rotation

## Code Example

```javascript
class VaultCache {
  constructor(fetchFn, ttlMs = 60000) {
    this.fetchFn = fetchFn;
    this.ttl = ttlMs;
    this.cache = new Map();
  }
  async get(key) {
    const now = Date.now();
    const cached = this.cache.get(key);
    if (cached && now - cached.ts < this.ttl) return cached.value;
    const value = await this.fetchFn(key);
    this.cache.set(key, { value, ts: now });
    return value;
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you test cache invalidation after Vault rotation?
- What metrics would you monitor to ensure no stale secrets are used during load?

